Politics Title: A group of Iowa State University professors have sued the federal government over Amendment 1A -- requiring voters to present a Photo ID when voting. 
 Text: [Their complaint](reads like an attack copy). Here it is in full:&amp;nbsp; 

 Providing this access could significantly increase minority participation at last year's elections. This access, they argue, violates the Equal Protection Clause which prohibits any law or practice having the effect of unreasonably impairing citizen's right to vote, and that decision "shall be made by the relevant individual States without regard to state constitutional amendments regarding eligibility for voting on account of race or color." They cite U.S. v. Lopez, 498 U. S. ___ , 2015 - No. 15-991. The same groups represented two similar suits against Texas after passing tough anti-voter
